{"id":661538,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arnold_Kopelson","text":"Arnold Kopelson (February 14, 1935 \u2013 October 8, 2018) was an American movie producer. He was born in Brooklyn, New York. He was known for his works in \"Platoon\", \"Seven\", \"Outbreak\", \"The Fugitive\" and \"The Devil's Advocate\".\nKopelson died at his home in Beverly Hills, California on October 8, 2018, aged 83.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":61},{"uri":"Movie_producer","surface_form":"movie producer","offset":70},{"uri":"Brooklyn","surface_form":"Brooklyn","offset":101},{"uri":"New_York_(state)","surface_form":"New York","offset":111},{"uri":"Platoon_(movie)","surface_form":"Platoon","offset":152},{"uri":"Seven_(movie)","surface_form":"Seven","offset":163},{"uri":"Outbreak_(movie)","surface_form":"Outbreak","offset":172},{"uri":"The_Fugitive_(1993_movie)","surface_form":"The Fugitive","offset":184},{"uri":"The_Devil%27s_Advocate_(1997_movie)","surface_form":"The Devil's Advocate","offset":203},{"uri":"Beverly_Hills%2C_California","surface_form":"Beverly Hills, California","offset":255}]}